Heat oven and cookie sheet to 400 degrees F. Stir pie crust mix and 1/3 cup cold water until dough forms a ball. Roll out half of dough into a 10 1/2-inch circle. Fold dough in half and place in 9-inch pie plate. Unfold and press into plate. Mix sugar, cornstarch and cinnamon in a bowl. Place apples in another bowl. Sprinkle mixture over apples and toss; spoon into the pie crust. Roll out remaining dough. Place over apples. Trim edges. Roll top edges under lower and pinch for a decorative edge. Cut 4 to 5 slits in top. Bake for 45 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 1 hour. Serve pie slices with a drizzle of warm caramel apple dip and a sprinkle of pecans.